messages.content:
Similar to **Glare**, which means always good, but with a different upgrade.
  Champ also has pretty good synergy with playing Skills so it works pretty well with that.
 Also it is only **Vulnerable** card that doesn't consume **Vigor** when played, which makes provides with with identity of its own.
 In addition to that it also is pretty good when it comes to extending the debuffs from **<Piledriver>** indefinitely.
 And Champ generally has problems with actually getting good **Block** numbers from cards, and in that scenario **Weak** ends up being incredibly good.

Deal 10 (14) damage.

Apply 2 **Weak:p_weak:**.
**:finisher:**   **Finisher**

messages.content: I view this as one of champs more niche cards. With vulnerable on several cards in his kit There are 2 good things about this card. First as a zero cost skill it cannot be bad by default simply for its abitily to trigger a stance bonus. Second with champs vulnerable sources being in attacks besides this; this is your only way to apply vulnerable without losing your vigor. This means that Taunt can find a place in decks that spefically want to save up vigor and one shot the enemy; with taunt bringing that big attack sooner and still providing skill point bonus when its not.
Besides that, there really isnt much going for taunt. champ has vulnerable built into serveral attacks already and as a low impact skill its hard to put into most decks.

just a question:
has Taunt+ ever been significant for you

Aoe weak has, just not aoe vulnerable (due to the context I use taunt in). I have taken a taunt + in runs were I skipped a normal taunt; although I don't think I have deliberately upgraded the card before.
taunt + is kind of like an intimidate that wont exhaust
truth be told, I haven't had Taunt+ be significant for me
mostly because I can unga bunga well enough with Fan of Knives that aoe Weak isn't useful
a lot of the time, taunts only really helping because its a zero cost skill rather then what the text acutally says. Champ just really values skill cards.
Taunt+ is half a Trip+ and half a Blind+
I like both trip and blind on champ a lot. basically for the same reason I use taunt. only those cards are just well better
It pairs really well with face slap and that's usually what I use it for
There's also the weaken card
That it can pair well with
